# Normalize line endings to LF in the repo (stops the per-commit CRLF warning flood on Windows).
# Existing files keep CRLF in the working tree until a one-time `git add --renormalize .` — run that
# in a quiet moment (it produces a large eol-only diff) to clear the warnings for good.
* text=auto eol=lf
# Binaries: never touch.
*.png binary
*.gif binary
*.webm binary
*.mp4 binary
README.md text eol=lf
docs/PRODUCTION_GUARANTEE_MATRIX.md text eol=lf
